  "texts": [
    "Instead, the nodes in the knowledge graph symbolize various entities found within the text, such as \"Ocean\" and \"Forest\".",
    "Conversely, the edges denote the relationships between these textual entities, expressing associations like \"Belongs to\" and \"Similar to\".",
    "Based on the entities from the previously acquired multi-document texts, when automatically constructing a knowledge graph, it is necessary to establish the index of the knowledge graph according to the attributes of the entities.",
    "The process of building multi-document knowledge graph is as follows:(1) Input the stored entities.",
    "A random entity X is selected from the text entities as the initial center point of the knowledge graph."
  ],
